# No private infrastructure in the repo

Committed examples, docs, defaults, and comments must not expose real private
infrastructure.

## Do

- Use RFC 2606 / documentation names: `example.com`, `app.example.com`, `admin@example.com`
- Prefer placeholders: `<server_name>`, `$HOME/...`, env overrides (`HOME_NGINX_CONF`, …)
- Keep live values in gitignored `conf/` (or host-local paths) only

## Do not

- Commit real personal/org domains (e.g. `*.hcma.info`, `*.house.*`)
- Commit real emails, machine hostnames, LAN IPs, or operator home directory paths
  as illustrative defaults in tracked files
- Paste inventory from a live host into examples “for convenience”

Repo / GitHub org URLs that identify this project (e.g. links to this repository)
are fine; **service hostnames and operator identity are not**.
